%N A272084 Number of ordered ways to write n as x^2 + y^2 + z^2 + w^2 with 4*x^2 + 5*y^2 + 20*z*w a square, where x,y,z,w are nonnegative integers with z < w.
%C A272084 Conjecture: (i) a(n) > 0 for all n > 0, and a(n) = 1 only for n = 2^k*q (k = 0,1,2,... and q = 1, 3, 7), 4^k*m (k = 0,1,2,... and m = 21, 30, 38, 62, 70, 77, 142, 217, 237, 302, 382, 406, 453, 670).
%C A272084 (ii) For each triple (a,b,c) = (1,8,8), (7,9,-12), (9,40,-24), (9,40,-60), any positive integer can be written as x^2 + y^2 + z^2 + w^2 with a*x^2 + b*y^2 + c*z*w a square, where w is a positive integer and x,y,z are nonnegative integers.
%C A272084 (iii) Any natural number can be written as x^2 + y^2 + z^2 + w^2 with (3*x+5*y)^2 -24*z*w a square, where x,y,z,w are nonnegative integers.  Also, for each ordered pair (a,b) = (1,4), (1,8), (1,12), (1,24), (1,32), (1,48), (25,24), (1,-4), (9,-4), (121,-20), every natural number can be written as x^2 + y^2 + z^2 + w^2 with a*x^2 + b*y*z a square, where x,y,z,w are nonnegative integers.
%C A272084 (iv) Any natural number can be written as x^2 + y^2 + z^2 + w^2 with (x^2-y^2)*(w^2-2*z^2) (or (x^2-y^2)*(2*w^2-z^2) or (x^2-y^2)*(w^2-5*z^2)) a square, where w,x,y,z are integers.
%C A272084 See also A262357, A268507, A269400, A271510, A271513, A271518, A271665, A271714, A271721, A271724, A271775, A271778 and A271824 for other conjectures refining Lagrange's four-square theorem.
